  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Patient diagnosed as Diagnostic and Statistical Manual of Mental Disorder, 4th
             edition, as paranoid, disorganized or undifferentiated type of schizophrenia in acute
             episode

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients previously treated with amisulpride

          -  Patients have comorbidity which may interfere with the treatment or follow-up

          -  Patients currently taking depot antipsychotics (at least 30 days washout period is
             needed)

          -  Patients currently/ or recently (&lt; 3 months) withdrawn from drug or alcohol abuse

          -  Pregnant or lactation

        The above information is not intended to contain all considerations relevant to a patient's
        potential participation in a clinical trial.
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
